# Suite, Project, Phase Terminology (Approved 2026-05)

Principal-approved vocabulary for LiNKaios project/process surfaces and integrations. **Do not reintroduce legacy names in new user-facing work.**

## LiNKaios hierarchy (user-facing)

| Level | Term | Was (legacy) | Meaning |
|-------|------|--------------|---------|
| 1 | **Suite** | Module (catalogue) | Subscribed product package (LinkSites, LiNKapps, …) |
| 2 | **Module** | Process / project type | Vendor-published recipe inside a suite (phases, issues, assignees) |
| 3 | **Project** | Project (was often “Mission” in code) | Tenant-created live work: one or more modules, once or continuous |
| 4 | **Phase** | Workflow | Stage group inside a module — a “mini workflow” within the module |
| 5 | **Issue** | Issue | Governed task (input/output contracts) |
| 6 | **Assignee** | Execution | Who runs the issue: LiNKbot, Automation, or Human |
| 7 | **Run** | (new standard) | One pass through project modules (continuous mode); maps to Plane **Cycle** in sync |

**Run once vs continuous:** Once = single end-to-end progress; Continuous = repeated **Runs** (no parallel runs in MVO).

## Capabilities (not “connectors” in LiNKaios UI)

In LiNKaios, integrations to external software (Plane, Odoo, Zulip, n8n, etc.) are **Capabilities**, governed by LinkSkills leases. Code paths may say `capability-connectors/`; user-facing copy says **Capabilities**.

| Capability (examples) | Software | MVO posture |
|----------------------|----------|-------------|
| `cap.plane.execution_tracking` | Plane (self-hosted) | mock/shadow; live writes future |
| `cap.crm.odoo_shadow` | Odoo CRM | mock/shadow; connector exists |
| `cap.accounting.odoo_shadow` | Odoo Accounting | mock/shadow; connector exists |
| `cap.zulip.run_messaging` | Zulip | governed messaging |
| LiNKautowork / n8n | Automations | executions via capability leases |

Do not ask Principal to “invent” Odoo integration — use existing capability contracts; extend modes (live) when approved.

## Backend “kitchen” systems (do not duplicate in LiNKaios)

| System | Role | LiNKaios must not |
|--------|------|-------------------|
| **Plane** (self-hosted) | Project/task board, cycles, assignees | Rebuild kanban, full issue editing |
| **Odoo** (CRM + accounting) | CRM records, invoices, ledger | Mirror full CRM/accounting UI |
| **n8n** (self-hosted, LiNKautowork) | Deterministic automations | Call n8n “workflows” in UI — use **Automation** |
| **Zulip** | LiNKbot communication | Rebuild chat |

## External terminology mapping

| LiNKaios | Plane (self-hosted) | Odoo | n8n | Zulip |
|----------|---------------------|------|-----|-------|
| Suite | *(none)* | App (do not confuse with LiNKaios Module) | — | — |
| Module | **Module** (work group in project) | — | — | — |
| Project | **Project** | Project (when linked) | — | **Stream** (one stream per LiNKaios project) |
| Phase | Epic or ordered work items under Plane module | — | Internal graph grouping | **Topic** (sub-threads inside project stream) |
| Issue | Work item | Task (when linked) | — | Referenced in topic messages |
| Assignee | Plane user (one service user per LiNKbot role) | — | Automation executor | — |
| Run | **Cycle** | — | Execution (internal) | — |

**Plane assignees (MVO):** One Plane user per LiNKbot role. Human-required steps: **Open in Plane** on issue row.

**Zulip (approved):** One **stream per LiNKaios Project**; **topics** inside that stream for sub-threads (phases, issues, operator threads).

**n8n (approved):** User-facing label **Automation**. **Phase** is LiNKaios module stage groups only.

