## UI surfaces (approved)

| Surface | Content |
|---------|---------|
| **My Suites → [Suite] → Modules** tab | Vendor **module catalogue** tree only: Module → Phase → Issue → Assignee (template) |
| **My Suites → [Suite] → Projects** tab | Compact active **projects** → project detail page |
| **Projects → All Projects** | One row per project; **Open LiNKaios project** OR **Open Plane**; sync as indicator |
| **Project detail page** | Single source of truth: progress, Plane snapshot, live tree, outputs/traces |

Do **not** put active project trees on the suite **Modules** catalogue tab.

## Plane capability defaults (approved — studio-provided for MVO)

**Ownership:** Plane is **bundled with LiNKaios** as the default project-management system for licensees. Customers do **not** supply Plane URL/API keys in MVO. Studio ops store Plane connection secrets in **Google Secret Manager**; LiNKaios reads them at runtime via the **`cap.plane.execution_tracking`** capability.

**Future:** A licensee bringing their own Plane (or another PM system) is a **later capability/lease** — not MVO tenant settings.

**Bootstrap on project launch (Option A):** Create an **empty Plane project**, then programmatically add Plane modules (LiNKaios modules), issues, and cycles (Runs) from suite templates.

**Customer Settings → API/secrets:** For **customer-owned** integrations only (their CRM keys, etc.) — **not** for studio-provided Plane in MVO.

## Forbidden in new user-facing copy

- **Mission** — use **Project**
- **Execution** (level label) — use **Assignee**
- **Workflow** for LiNKaios phase groups — use **Phase**
- **Workflow** for n8n in UI — use **Automation**
- **Process** for vendor templates — use **Module**
- **Module** for LinkSites product — use **Suite**
- **Cycle** in LiNKaios UI — use **Run**
- **Connector** in LiNKaios UI — use **Capability**

Legacy symbols (`missionId`, `MissionRecord`, old `/modules/` routes) may persist until migration phases C/D complete.

